## PLAN-GATE CORRECTION (Tier-1 gate, 3-seat: codex BLOCK verified-true; Opus GO; gemini seat-crashed (internal ripgrep regex error) — no verdict, re-run at implement gate)
codex caught a real over-restriction, verified at capture_run.go:193: `specDir := filepath.Dir(specPath)` is RELATIVE when the user runs `etude capture-run spec.yaml` (specDir == "."). Go's filepath.EvalSymlinks keeps a relative input relative UNLESS a component is an absolute symlink. So for a LEGIT inside-pointing symlink with an ABSOLUTE target (a.md -> /abs/specdir/sub/b.md), EvalSymlinks(resolved) becomes absolute while EvalSymlinks(".") stays ".", and filepath.Rel(".", "/abs/...") ERRORS → the legit inside symlink is falsely REJECTED (violates the accept-inside-symlinks requirement). (The escape THREAT is still caught — Rel error → deny — so this is an over-restriction/usability bug, not a security hole, but it must be fixed.)

REQUIRED FIX — anchor everything on an ABSOLUTE lexical base before realpath comparison:
1. In run() (before the stage loop, right after `specDir := filepath.Dir(specPath)` at :193): compute `absSpecDir, err := filepath.Abs(specDir)` (handle err), then `realSpecDir, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(absSpecDir)` (handle err — a missing/unresolvable spec dir is a hard error). Thread BOTH absSpecDir (the lexical absolute base) and realSpecDir (the realpath base) through buildStage to resolveArtifactPath.
2. In resolveArtifactPath: reject absolute relPath (unchanged); resolve against the ABSOLUTE base: `resolved := filepath.Clean(filepath.Join(absSpecDir, relPath))` (now absolute); lexical Rel-confine `resolved` against `absSpecDir` (the existing cheap pre-check, now on absolute paths); then `realResolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(resolved)` (err → "escapes the spec directory", deny-by-default); then Rel-confine `realResolved` against `realSpecDir`. Both sides absolute → Rel never errors spuriously. Return realResolved (TOCTOU mitigation, unchanged).

REQUIRED ADDED TEST: a POSITIVE case — invoke capture-run with a RELATIVE spec path (e.g. chdir into the spec dir, run `capture-run spec.yaml`) where an artifact is a symlink with an ABSOLUTE target pointing INSIDE the spec dir → must be ACCEPTED (proves the relative-base fix). Keep all other tests from the matrix.

Signature becomes resolveArtifactPath(absSpecDir, realSpecDir, relPath). All other plan decisions stand (lexical-then-realpath, Rel-based predicate, deny-by-default, return realpath, the reject-outside test matrix, docs/capture-run.md 1-line update, no docs/cli regen).
